quran[13]{c,v,t}:
  2,47,"Children of Israel, remember My blessing wherewith I blessed you, and that I have preferred you above all beings"
  2,48,"and beware of a day when no soul for another shall give satisfaction, and no intercession shall be accepted from it, nor any counterpoise be taken, neither shall they be helped"
  2,49,"And when We delivered you from the folk of Pharaoh who were visiting you with evil chastisement, slaughtering your sons, and sparing your women; and in that was a grievous trial from your Lord"
  2,50,"And when We divided for you the sea and delivered you, and drowned Pharaoh's folk while you were beholding"
  2,51,And when We appointed with Moses forty nights then you took to yourselves the Calf after him and you were evildoers
  2,52,"then We pardoned you after that, that haply you should be thankful"
  2,53,"And when We gave to Moses the Book and the Salvation, that haply you should be guided"
  2,54,"And when Moses said to his people, 'My people, you have done wrong against yourselves by your taking the Calf; now turn to your Creator and slay one another. That will be better for you in your Creator's sight, and He will turn to you; truly He turns, and is All-compassionate"
  2,55,"And when you said, 'Moses, we will not believe thee till we see God openly'; and the thunderbolt took you while you were beholding"
  2,56,"Then We raised you up after you were dead, that haply you should be thankful"
  2,57,"And We outspread the cloud to overshadow you, and We sent down manna and quails upon you: 'Eat of the good things wherewith We have provided you. And they worked no wrong upon Us, but themselves they wronged"
  2,58,"And when We said, 'Enter this township, and eat easefully of it wherever you will, and enter in at the gate, prostrating, and say, Unburdening; We will forgive you your transgressions, and increase the good-doers"
  2,59,Then the evildoers substituted a saying other than that which had been said to them; so We sent down upon the evildoers wrath out of heaven for their ungodliness